Nice and all, but it still doesn't follow that it must be useful in every zone. While a pet doing more of it's damage via spells is ok, that still doesn't mean it has to, or even should, be useful in every zone. And none of the spells it casts should, as has been suggested, be lures. The whole reason for lures for wizards is basically this: We don't get a pet. It gives us a way to work around not being able to damage mobs that are abnormally spell resistant. And even then, there are some mobs that have resisted lures fairly well too. You get pets and malosini to work around that issue, therefore you shouldn't get lures and neither should your pet. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4380">Qaman</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
