<br>
Draughts, Lures and Ice Comet are not nessecary to make that pet usefull, but it would turn the pet into a burst Dps pet. (Though not realiable.)<br>
<br>
Burst Dps on the other hand is the 'Realm' of Wizards, that is why we got Lures and Draughts. It sound not right to raise Mage's burst Dps via a pet, since ALL of your pets are doing sustained damage and your nukes on top of the pet damage are aleady some kind of burst Dps.<br>
<br>
One more time my sugestion for a 'usefull' fire pet:<br>
<br>
Make it casting only, no melee.<br>
Make it AE immune, if nessecary.<br>
Root it, if nessecary.<br>
<br>
Put the following spells on it:<br>
Conflag<br>
Force Strike<br>
Lightning Shock<br>
Elnericks Entombment of Ice<br>
Ice Shock<br>
<br>
This are allmost all of our main nukes for level 34 to 44. As you see, we don't get that many. But if the pet is only casting and not meleeing this is much more than sufficient to reach 80+ DPS.<br>
<br>
Lures, Draughts and 'Big bangs', our class defining abbilities that set us apart from Mages (and enable us to do burst damage), don't belong on a Mage pet. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=qaman>Qaman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 3195<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/21/03 10:41 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: thought you should hear it from a mage first</span><hr size=1> &gt;A range of 300+ for its spells will make sure it can nuke from out of AE range (if they don´t want to add AE immunities - which they took away from our pets with PoP). <br>
